12. Marsus, Domitius Marsus was a younger contempo- rary of Horace. He wrote erotie elegies and an epie, Amazonis, IV. 29. 7, besides epigrams. He is often mentioned by Martial.

Pedo Albinovanus, a friend of Ovid, and author of a Theseis as well as of epigrams. He was a scholarly poet, doctique Pedonis, 11. 77. 5, and a brilliant talker‚ Seneca, Ep. 122. 15, ‘fabulator eleyantissimus!
